      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How long is title insurance valid?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">An owner's title insurance policy is valid for as long as you or your heirs own the property. A lender's policy is valid for the life of the loan. There are no renewal fees or expiration dates.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I shop around for title insurance?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Yes! In Utah, you have the right to choose your title company. While rates are regulated and similar across companies, service quality, communication, and convenience can vary significantly. We encourage you to compare.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What happens if a title claim is filed?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">If someone challenges your ownership or a covered defect is discovered, you contact your title insurance company. They will investigate the claim and either resolve the issue, defend your ownership in court, or compensate you for covered losses — at no additional cost to you.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do I need title insurance for a cash purchase?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">While there's no lender requiring it, an owner's policy is still strongly recommended for cash purchases. Without a mortgage company's lender policy requirement, the owner's policy is your only line of defense against title defects.</div>
      </details>

